## Les Mills BODYJAM™

Hear the latest music. Learn the freshest moves. Lose yourself and just dance.

## Les Mills GRIT™

GRIT is a result-driven 30-minute high intensity interval training (HIIT) workout, designed to improve strength, cardiovascular fitness and build lean muscle.

## Les Mills TONE™

Fuses functional training with cardio, resistance, and core to create a workout with options for increasing intensity as endurance and strength increase.

## PowerStep 

Incorporates advanced cardio step moves, intervals, and creative use of the step for a full-body blast.

## Step on Up 

Focuses on intermediate step moves and core conditioning.

## Zumba 

Blends the best of Latin and worldly beats to provide the pulse to raise yours.

## HIIT Cardio 

Chase your goals through intervals that include running, lateral movement, rotational movement, on/off the floor work, all in under 30 minutes.

## KICKBOX Yoga Fusion 

Combine martial arts techniques with cardio and conditioning. Then re-center and breathe in an abbreviated yoga practice.

Cycle 

## Beginner Power Ride 

Spend some extra time at the start of class getting hands-on assistance setting up your bike, ride an extended warmup, then shift your training for a 45-minute ride varying intervals, resistance, and speed in this class suited for beginners and veterans alike!

## Power Ride 

Shift your training through varying intervals, resistance, and speed as you simulate an athletic, outdoor ride in this indoor cycle class.

## Performance Ride 

Improve your performance with this data-driven interval class utilizing the SPIVI system to focus on your metrics. Compete against your own numbers or those on the board, climbing your way to the top.

## HIIT Cycle 

Improve your stamina and speed in less than 30 minutes a pop with quick bursts of intense work with short rounds of recovery.

## Les Mills RPM™

Combines hill climbs, sprints and flat riding, creating an ever-changing journey to improved strength, speed and fitness.

## Les Mills SPRINT™

Drives the body to burn calories for hours through max effort HIIT training on the bike in only 30 minutes.

## Virtual RPM™

Cycling workout where you control the intensity. Dial up the challenge factor to match your fitness level.

## Virtual SPRINT™

High-intensity interval training on a bike. It’s a short 30-minute, intense style of training where the thrill and motivation comes from pushing your physical and mental limits.

## Virtual The TRIP™

A totally unique 45-minute workout experience that combines a multi-peak cycling workout with a journey through digitally-created worlds.

## Vybe Ride 

An epic journey, featuring drama in the music, thumping bass, and catchy lyrics as you ride to the beat on the bike.

Mind Body 

## Beginner Yoga 

If you have felt out of place in a yoga class before or didn’t know where to start but wanted to add yoga practice to your fitness life, this is the place to start. Receive personal attention, assistance, cues, and safety refinements to move in and out of the basic poses, along with learning breath and meditation practices, so you feel confident to try other yoga classes. We recommend you bring your own mat and wear clothing that is comfortable to move in.

## Hatha Yoga 

Hatha Yoga is a practice that combines yoga postures and breathing exercises to help bring peace to the mind and body.

## Les Mills BODYBALANCE™

Blends yoga, tai chi, Pilates and stretching to reduce stress, increase flexibility, improve strength and increase mind-body awareness.

## MAT Pilates 

Delivers big changes in flexibility, alignment, core strength, coordination and balance through small movements in smaller muscles.

## Mat Pilates/Barre Fusion 

Delivers big changes in flexibility, alignment, core strength, coordination and balance through small movements in Get the best of both worlds! Start off with central powerhouse focused work with a Mat Pilates series followed by Barre work. Focus on small, controlled movement to find length and strength in your body.

## Yoga for Athletes 

When you are athletic and strong, many professionals will suggest some sort of yoga or mobility practice to increase your range of motion and recovery from intense workouts. Yoga for athletes helps target muscle asymmetry, which can cause imbalances, through flexibility exercises, stretching, and enhanced range of motion movements. We will enhance all these functionalities, and learn to integrate them into a flow to enhance your ability to adapt to different muscle strengths and coordination more quickly. No yoga experience necessary!

## Power Yoga 

Power Yoga is a vigorous practice that synchronizes the breath with a progressive series of postures, a process that increases internal heat, creating a purifying sweat, that detoxifies muscles and organs. The result is improved circulation, a strong body, and a calm mind.

## Restorative Yoga 

Focuses on relaxing the body in slower, restful postures, allowing the body to renew and heal.

## Sunrise Yoga 

This early morning practice synchronizes breath with flowing, dynamic movement and centers you for the day ahead.

## TRX Yoga 

Improves balance, flexibility and mindfulness with the help of the TRX strap through a series of yoga moves designed to assist those newer to practice and to deepen the practice of experienced yogis.

## Vinyasa Yoga 

Synchronizes breath with flowing, dynamic movement.

## Yin Yoga 

Yin yoga targets your deep connective tissues, like your fascia, ligaments, joints, and bones. It’s slower and more meditative, giving you space to turn inward and tune into both your mind and the physical sensations of your body.

## Yoga Fundamentals 

Uses a slower pace to focus on proper form and alignment in poses to create greater understanding and deepen practice.

## Yoga Sculpt 

Fuses strength, intensity, cardio and hand weights with the mental and emotional focus of a traditional yoga practice.

Strength Training 

## B’More Active 

Includes low-impact cardio,

# Tips to Get Started

[Image 8: Core_Cycle_Studios_Timonium_Maryland_Yoga_Barre.jpg]   

### Fuel Up 

Come well hydrated with plenty of water and a light snack. Forgot your water, no worries. Our fridge is fully stocked with Defiance Fuel, the ultimate rehydration tool!

### Arrive On Time 

Please arrive at the studio 10-15 minutes before your first class, so we can give you a tour of the studio and introduce to your instructor. If you are riding for the first-time we strongly encourage you to arrive 20 minutes before your first class.

### Sign In 

Before your first class, you need to sign a waiver. If you are under 18, you need one signed by a parent in person.

### Jump In 

Our team will help to outfit you with shoes and sock, and adjust your bike and props. Water-check! Towel-check! You’re ready to rock your class!

### Get Moving 

Follow your CCS instructor and let the music carry you through the entire class. There is no judgement, no egos, and it’s ok to recover whenever you feel you need it. Want the class playlist, just ask your instructor and she will send it to you to help you keep rocking your day!

### Keep Track 

If you are riding with us, after your ride we’ll send you an email with your performance stats to help you meet and crush your riding goals.

parts:
Here are some great options for group fitness classes near the 21093 area:

1. **Brick Bodies Padonia**:
   - Offers a variety of group fitness classes, including Les Mills BODYJAM™, Zumba, HIIT Cardio, PowerStep, and various yoga and cycling classes like Beginner Yoga, Power Yoga, and RPM™. They have specialized studios for different types of workouts and provide an immersive experience with custom lighting and sound【11†source】【12†source】.

2. **Jazzercise Lutherville Fitness Center**:
   - This center focuses on dance-based fitness classes. They offer a range of Cardio Sculpt and Power Sculpt sessions that blend cardio, strength training, and dance to create a fun and effective workout routine【13†source】.

3. **Core Cycle Studios**:
   - A boutique fitness studio offering cycle, barre, and yoga classes. The studio emphasizes community and personalized attention, making it a great place for both beginners and advanced participants to find challenging and rewarding workouts【14†source】.

4. **Titan CrossFit**:
   - Located in Cockeysville, Titan CrossFit offers a variety of CrossFit classes, personal training, and nutrition coaching. They cater to all fitness levels and have a strong community focus. Classes include strength training, Olympic weightlifting, and specialized programs for teens and kids【15†source】.

These options provide a range of fitness experiences from high-intensity interval training and dance-based workouts to yoga and cycling, ensuring you can find something that fits your preferences and fitness goals.
